{"title":"How to watch La Flèche Wallonne 2024","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/watch-fleche-wallonne","date":1713196228000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/watch-fleche-wallonne\">How to watch La Flèche Wallonne 2024</a></p>\n\n<p>We have reached the sandwich filling of the Ardennes week: <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/la-fleche-wallonne-preview\" target=\"_blank\">La Flèche Wallonne</a>. The middle child of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/opinion-ardennes-classics\" target=\"_blank\">the Ardennes</a>, La Flèche Wallonne is understated in its nature, but its brutal finale up the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/mur-de-huy-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">Mur de Huy</a> never goes unnoticed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Taking place on Wednesday 17th April, the men’s and women’s Flèches Wallonnes proposes a tough battle through the Ardennais hills. The men’s 199km-long race in the morning will give a teaser of what’s to come for the women’s peloton later in the afternoon.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Both races promise star-billing, with defending women’s champion Demi Vollering (SD Worx-Protime) down to start in Huy on Wednesday. The men’s race won’t see its reigning champion return to the Mur de Huy, so the title of La Flèche is truly up for grabs.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/opinion-ardennes-classics\">Opinion: Put some respect on the Ardennes Classics’ name</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/la-fleche-wallonne-preview\">La Flèche Wallonne 2024: Routes, how to watch, start list and everything you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/liege-bastogne-liege-route-riders-and-all-you-need-to-know\">Liège-Bastogne-Liège 2024: Route, riders, how to watch and all you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>How to watch men’s and women’s Flèches Wallonnes 2024</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"728\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/pogacar-podium-2323-edited-970x728.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/pogacar-podium-2323-edited-970x728.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/pogacar-podium-2323-edited-300x225.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/pogacar-podium-2323-edited-768x576.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/pogacar-podium-2323-edited-1536x1153.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/pogacar-podium-2323-edited-750x563.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/pogacar-podium-2323-edited-1140x856.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/pogacar-podium-2323-edited.png 1599w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O./Maxime Delobel</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Flèches Wallonnes 2024 (yes, that’s the plural form) will be available to watch in the UK on Eurosport and <a href=\"https://auth.discoveryplus.com/gb/product?flow=purchase&amp;videoAssetId=6021174\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a> for £6.99 per month with the basic package, which includes cycling and all other Eurosport programmes. Both races will also be shown live in the UK on the TV channel Eurosport 1.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s not being shown in your country, you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while abroad in countries without access.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One such example is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is very <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, helps users to find a way to watch cycling without having to pay for broadcasters services, and costs £5.36 per month, with three months free. Other options include <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fnordvpn.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">NordVPN</a>, <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fsurfshark.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Surfshark</a> and <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kaspersky.co.uk%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Kapersky</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Read more: <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">How to watch cycling post-GCN</a></strong> </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Full list of broadcasters</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"546\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/mur-de-huy-fleche-edited-970x546.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/mur-de-huy-fleche-edited-970x546.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/mur-de-huy-fleche-edited-300x169.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/mur-de-huy-fleche-edited-768x432.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/mur-de-huy-fleche-edited-750x422.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/mur-de-huy-fleche-edited-1140x641.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/mur-de-huy-fleche-edited.png 1280w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O/Billy Ceusters</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4>Men’s race</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Australia: </strong>SBS<br /><strong>Belgium: </strong>RTBF La Une, VRT Eén<br /><strong>Canada:</strong> FloBikes<br /><strong>China:</strong> Zhibo TV<br /><strong>Colombia:</strong> Caracol TV<br /><strong>Denmark: </strong>TV2<br /><strong>Europe: </strong>Eurosport<br /><strong>France: </strong>France 3, Eurosport France<br /><strong>Italy: </strong>Rai Sport<br /><strong>Japan: </strong>J Sports<br /><strong>Latin America and Caribbean: </strong>ESPN International <br /><strong>Luxembourg:</strong> RTL<br /><strong>Middle East &amp; North Africa:</strong> beIN Sports<br /><strong>Netherlands:</strong> NOS<br /><strong>Norway: </strong>TV2<br /><strong>Slovakia: </strong>RTVS<br /><strong>South East Asia: </strong>Eurosport 1<br /><strong>Spain:</strong> Teledeporte<br /><strong>Sub-Saharan Africa: </strong>Supersport<br /><strong>Switzerland: </strong>SRG-SSR<br /><strong>United States: </strong>NBC Sports</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Women’s race</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Australia:</strong> SBS<br /><strong>Belgium:</strong> RTBF, VRT<br /><strong>Canada: </strong>FloBikes<br /><strong>Colombia: </strong>Señal Colombia<br /><strong>Denmark:</strong> TV2<br /><strong>Europe:</strong> Eurosport<br /><strong>France:</strong> France Television<br /><strong>Italy:</strong> Rai Sport<br /><strong>Japan:</strong> J Sports<br /><strong>Latin America and Caribbean:</strong> ESPN International<br /><strong>Netherlands: </strong>NOS<br /><strong>New Zealand: </strong>Sky Sport<br /><strong>Norway: </strong>TV2<br /><strong>South East Asia: </strong>Eurosport 1<br /><strong>Sub-Saharan Africa:</strong> Supersport<br /><strong>United States: </strong>NBC Sports</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>La Flèche Wallonne 2024: What time does coverage start?</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"1280\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/eenkhoorn-fleche-edited.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/eenkhoorn-fleche-edited.png 1280w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/eenkhoorn-fleche-edited-300x188.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/eenkhoorn-fleche-edited-970x606.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/eenkhoorn-fleche-edited-768x480.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/eenkhoorn-fleche-edited-750x469.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/eenkhoorn-fleche-edited-1140x713.png 1140w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O/Billy Ceusters</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>All times BST and subject to change by broadcasters.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Men’s Flèche Wallonne</h4>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Discovery+:</strong> 11:45 – 15:55</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 13:30 – 15:30</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h4>Women’s Flèche Wallonne</h4>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Eurosport 1</strong> 15:55 – 17:00</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong><strong>Discovery</strong>+:</strong> 15:55 – 17:15</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Like Flèche Wallonne? Read our article on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/mur-de-huy-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">just how hard the Mur de Huy is</a>.</em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/watch-fleche-wallonne\">How to watch La Flèche Wallonne 2024</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Ewan Wilson","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"8a3be225bc4bb7a94921627512edfeb10292117e8098527fc30aa92ad09a9c3e","category":"Cycling"}